summary.overview:
- Prediction agent successfully deployed on Olas network after 1.5 hours of extensive configuration; runs asynchronously 1-2 times daily.
- Complex token swapping process required five conversions due to ETH not being accepted; gas fees account for approximately 8% of total funds.
- Custom agents cannot be adjusted for database comparison projects; two strategies identified for future exploration: quality scoring and preference prediction.
- Primary focus on agent registration and deployment setup, requiring further research on custom creation; Vardhan to report findings next meeting.
- Plan to create eight databases (2x2x2) using all papers from two shared Google Drive folders to demonstrate system capabilities.
- Fixed-length chunking recommended to avoid formatting issues; pending verification of token limits for 'no chunking' option.
- Joe and Andrew rescheduled meeting from today to tomorrow at 7am; Vardhan to request a more suitable time.
- Gradio UI framework suggested as a new interface to address ongoing issues; public AI benchmarked with $8M Series A funding and $14M revenue.
- Laura approved funding for hiring an automated scientist developer via Athena DAO tokens; Vardhan tasked to find a candidate by week's end.
- Database sharing solution needed, weighing options between shared beta account and manual transfer method.

- Modular architecture and anti-regression mechanisms implemented in Django to enhance development stability.
- PostgreSQL chosen as the storage architecture for managing large transcript data effectively.
- Fireflies integration successfully querying and storing transcript data in PostgreSQL, enhancing data management capabilities.
- Connection to Monday.com testing board established, with admin panel modifications facilitating user management and system logging.
- Production deployment recommended to utilize Vercel for seamless GitHub integration, with a commitment for readiness by tomorrow evening.
- Twitter integration planning slated to follow Monday.com system completion, indicating a structured development roadmap.
